                        <pf>Judge</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Letter from James Skinner discusses how many voters in different counties
                    of the 9th congressional district were opposed to and how many approved of a
                    convention; claims that three-fourths of August supported one (1125) and
                    one-fourth did not (375). Sums up that a majority wanted a convention (2196
                    voters) and that allegations that it was called to "kill off" Harris are
                    ridiculous.</summary>
            </div>
